"\n    <!-- Session & Network Security -->\n    <session-layer>\n        <tls version=\"1.3\">\n        <mutual-auth required=\"true\">\n        <multi-factor-auth enabled=\"true\" factors=\"device-pki+password\">\n        <timeout value=\"600\" unit=\"seconds\">\n    </timeout></multi-factor-auth></mutual-auth></tls></session-layer>\n    <!-- SwarmNet Safe Orchestrator -->\n    <swarmnet-orchestrator>\n        <self-monitoring active=\"true\">\n        <self-healing>\n            <monitor type=\"performance, anomaly, hardware-health, logic-integrity\">\n            <auto-rollback trigger=\"worst-case.math\" restrict_external_control=\"true\">\n            <checkpointing enabled=\"true\" interval=\"5min\">\n            <recovery-policy mode=\"internal-only\" preapproved_resilience=\"yes\" rollback_threshold=\"marketvalue &amp; integrity risk\">\n        </recovery-policy></checkpointing></auto-rollback></monitor></self-healing>\n    </self-monitoring></swarmnet-orchestrator>\n    <!-- Console Main Components -->\n    <page-header>\n        <h1>Comet Console: Critical Admin Control</h1>\n        <div class=\"alert info\">\n            ALL ACCESS IS ENTERPRISE-BOUND, SYSTEM-ONLY, AND HARDWARE-ENFORCED.\n        </div>\n    </page-header>\n    <menu>\n        <item id=\"dashboard\">System Dashboard</item>\n        <item id=\"risk\">Risk/Anomaly Monitors</item>\n        <item id=\"healing\">Self-Healing &amp; Rollback</item>\n        <item id=\"audit\">Audit Logs (Immutable)</item>\n        <item id=\"device-mgmt\">Device/Member Bindings</item>\n    </menu>\n    <footer>\n        <legal>\n            <disclaimer>\n                Strict AI/Meta-layer compliance.
